  <chapter>
    <title>&package;</title>

    <refsect2 id="overview">
      <para>
        Emeus is a small library that provides a GTK+ container using
        constraints to lay out its children. Constraints are resolved
        at run time, depending on the value of the attributes they
        reference. By using Emeus, it's possible to create complex GUI
        layouts without using computing positions and sizes manually,
        and without using nested boxes to control spacing and alignment.
      </para>
    </refsect2>

